**Methodology (simple and clear):**

> The project follows a modular methodology. Initially, health-related datasets are collected and cleaned.
 Machine Learning models are trained on structured datasets and saved as pickle files. 
 Deep Learning CNN models are trained using image datasets and saved as H5 files. 
 Soft Computing is applied using fuzzy logic rules to handle uncertainty in asthma severity prediction. 
 A chatbot layer processes user input and routes it to the appropriate model. A closed-domain LLM generates simple explanations. 
 Finally, the system is integrated using a Streamlit web interface for user interaction.